Keywords: predictive regression, single-index model, Hermite orthogonal estimation, 
dual super-consistency rates, co-moving predictors.
Abstract: This paper studies a semiparametric single-index predictive regression model with
multiple nonstationary predictors that exhibit co-movement behaviour. Orthogonal series
expansion is employed to approximate the unknown link function in the model and the
estimator is derived from an optimization under constraint. The main finding includes
two types of super-consistency rates for the estimators of the index parameter. The
central limit theorem is established for a plug-in estimator of the unknown link function.
In the empirical studies, we provide ample evidence in favor of nonlinear predictability
of the stock return using four pairs of nonstationary predictors.
