Abstract: Accurate estimation for extent of cross-sectional dependence in large panel data analysis is paramount 
to further statistical analysis on the data under study. Grouping more data with weak relations (cross-sectional dependence) 
together often results in less efficient dimension reduction and worse forecasting. This paper describes cross-sectional 
dependence among a large number of objects (time series) via a factor model and parametrizes its extent in terms of 
